                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.18/34: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-28T16:00:00-06:00"
                            >February 28, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. The following telegram has been sent to the Legation in Costa Rica: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“February 28, 4 p.m. Your telegram February 28, 10 a.m. I have advised
                            the Minister for Foreign Affairs that there will be some <pb facs="0329"
                                n="236" xml:id="pg_236"/> delay in this matter but the attitude here
                            is such that I have thought it advisable to give him no further
                            information from your telegram or to make further representations in
                            this connection until I have received instructions from the Department
                            in reply to telegram I am sending it today. Repeated to the
                            Department.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
